Agents of Empires — License Map
================================

Copyright (c) 2026 Rabid Troll Studios LLC

This repository is intentionally licensed in THREE parts. Which license
applies depends on which part of the repository a file belongs to. When in
doubt, the most specific LICENSE file nearest a given file governs it.

  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Part                              License               Full text
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1. Agent SDK (the contract        MIT                   LICENSES/MIT.txt
     agents build against)                                UnityRTS/AgentSDK/LICENSE
     UnityRTS/AgentSDK/**

  2. Everything else — the engine,  AGPL-3.0-or-later     LICENSES/AGPL-3.0.txt
     headless harness, parity/         + AI-training      LICENSES/EXCEPTION-
     balance runners, Unity            exception          AI-TRAINING.txt
     front-end, tests, scripts

  3. Art assets                     MIT                   art/LICENSE
     art/**                            + AI-training      LICENSES/MIT.txt
     (AI-generated game art)           clause
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Why it's split this way
-----------------------

* The **Agent SDK is MIT** so that anyone can write, keep private, and even
  commercialize their own competing agents. Agents compile only against the
  SDK and run against the engine at arm's length (loaded as separate DLLs
  through the SDK interface). The copyleft on the engine does NOT reach
  through the SDK into your agent code. Your agent is yours.

* The **engine and everything else is AGPL-3.0**, so the platform stays open:
  anyone may use, modify, run, and even build a business around it, BUT any
  modified version they distribute OR run as a network service must be made
  available in full source under the same license. This prevents anyone from
  taking this code closed-source and shipping it as a proprietary product.
  (AGPL, rather than plain GPL, because this engine is designed to run as an
  online competition server — AGPL closes the "runs on a server, never
  distributed" loophole.)

* The **art is MIT**, deliberately maximally open — free for anyone,
  including teachers using it in class, with no restriction.

AI / machine-learning training is permitted for EVERYONE, everywhere
--------------------------------------------------------------------

Across ALL three parts of this repository — code and art alike — using the
material to develop, train, fine-tune, evaluate, or benchmark AI/ML models
(including competing agents) is expressly permitted, commercially, with no
attribution or additional permission required:

  * For the MIT parts (SDK and art), this is already granted by the MIT
    license's broad permission, reinforced by the AI-training clause in
    art/LICENSE.
  * For the AGPL part, this is granted by the AI-training exception in
    LICENSES/EXCEPTION-AI-TRAINING.txt (a Section 7 additional permission),
    which frees ML training/evaluation use from the copyleft obligations.

In short: you can train commercial models on the whole thing — art and code —
and so can anyone else. What you cannot do is take the ENGINE and turn it into
a closed-source product.

